---
import Base from "../layouts/Base.astro";
---

<Base title="About Pikos" description="Who built Pikos, why it exists, and the local-first philosophy behind it.">

  <main class="mx-auto max-w-2xl px-8 py-20">

    <!-- Back to home -->
    <a href="/" class="inline-flex items-center gap-1 text-sm text-gray-400 transition-colors hover:text-orange-500 dark:text-gray-500 dark:hover:text-orange-400">
      <svg xmlns="http://www.w3.org/2000/svg" width="14" height="14" viewBox="0 0 24 24" fill="none" stroke="currentColor" stroke-width="2" stroke-linecap="round" stroke-linejoin="round" aria-hidden="true"><path d="m15 18-6-6 6-6"/></svg>
      Home
    </a>

    <h1 class="mt-8 text-4xl font-bold tracking-tight text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">About Pikos</h1>

    <div class="mt-10 space-y-6 text-base leading-relaxed text-gray-600 dark:text-gray-300">
      <p>
        Pikos is built by <a href="https://alexking.dev" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">Alex King</a> — a solo developer who got tired of splitting his brain across three apps just to stay organized.
      </p>

      <p>
        Notes in one app. Tasks in another. Calendar in a third. Every day, the same dance: copy a task title into a calendar event, paste a meeting link into a note, wonder where you wrote that thing down. It's busywork disguised as productivity.
      </p>

      <p>
        Pikos puts notes, tasks, and your calendar in one place. A page can be all three at once — write about it, track it, schedule it. No converting, no switching, no syncing between apps.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">Local-first, no exceptions</h2>

      <p>
        Your data lives on your device. Not on our servers, not in someone else's cloud. Pikos stores everything in a local database on your machine. There's no account to create, no login, and no way for us to see what you write.
      </p>

      <p>
        Sync between your own devices uses iCloud — Apple's infrastructure, your Apple account. We never touch the data in transit or at rest. If you stop using Pikos tomorrow, your data is still right there on your disk.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">Buy once, own it</h2>

      <p>
        No subscription. You pay once and the app is yours. Updates included. No "free tier" that holds your data hostage until you upgrade. No dark patterns nudging you toward a plan you don't need.
      </p>

      <h2 class="pt-4 text-2xl font-semibold text-gray-900 dark:text-gray-50">Get in touch</h2>

      <p>
        Found a bug? Have a feature request? Just want to say hi? Reach out at
        <a href="mailto:hello@pikos.app" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">hello@pikos.app</a>.
      </p>
    </div>

    <!-- Footer -->
    <footer class="mt-20 border-t border-gray-100 pt-8 dark:border-gray-800">
      <div class="flex flex-wrap items-center justify-center gap-x-6 gap-y-2 text-sm text-gray-400 dark:text-gray-500">
        <a href="/" class="transition-colors hover:text-orange-500 dark:hover:text-orange-400">Home</a>
        <a href="/privacy" class="transition-colors hover:text-orange-500 dark:hover:text-orange-400">Privacy</a>
        <span>Pikos by <a href="https://alexking.dev" class="text-orange-500 hover:underline">Alex</a></span>
      </div>
    </footer>

  </main>
</Base>

<style>
  :global(body) {
    background-color: #fafaf9;
  }

  :global(html.dark body) {
    background-color: #030712;
  }
</style>
